         <abstract>
            <p>This paper deals with characterization of best approximations to vector-valued functions. The approximations are themselves vector-valued functions with components depending nonlinearly on the approximation parameters. The constraint is imposed that certain of the parameters should be identical for all components. An application to exponential approximation is discussed in some detail.</p>
          </abstract>
